HEADWORD: Clarichord
<hw>Clar"i*chord</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>clatocorde</ets>, fr.L. <ets>clarus</ets> clear + <ets>chorda</ets>
string. See <er>Chord</er>.]</ety> <def>A musical instrument, formerly
in use, in form of a spinet; -- called also <altname>manichord</altname>
and <altname>clavichord</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

